gaze to another place on the map. 'Here, for instance, is Egypt, the pyramids. And here is Spain where they do horrible things to bulls....'

Knowing that Luzhin had probably already been more than once in many of the towns they might have visited, she did not name the large cities in order to avoid any harmful reminiscences. A superfluous caution. The world in which Luzhin had traveled in his time was not depicted on the map, and if she had named him Rome or London, then from the sound of these